Package: arealDB
Title: Harmonise and Integrate Heterogeneous Areal Data
Description: Many relevant applications in the environmental and
        socioeconomic sciences use areal data, such as biodiversity
        checklists, agricultural statistics, or socioeconomic surveys.
        For applications that surpass the spatial, temporal or thematic
        scope of any single data source, data must be integrated from
        several heterogeneous sources. Inconsistent concepts,
        definitions, or messy data tables make this a tedious and
        error-prone process. 'arealDB' tackles those problems and helps
        the user to integrate a harmonised databases of areal data.
        Read the paper at Ehrmann, Seppelt & Meyer (2020)
        <doi:10.1016/j.envsoft.2020.104799>.
Version: 0.9.4
